definitions.definition: A group of people who sing together; a company of people who are trained to sing together.
examples: The church choir practices Thursday nights.

definitions.definition: Uncommon form of quire ( “ one quarter of a cruciform church, or the architectural area of a church used by the choir, often near the apse ” ) .
One of the nine ranks or orders of angels .
examples: Seraphim, Cherubim, and Thrones are three of the choirs of angels.

definitions.definition: Set of strings (one per note) for a harpsichord .
